msgid "Use of the Meson build system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:23
msgid "Updated SIMD support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:24
msgid "f2py fixes, meson and bind(x) support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:25 ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:44
msgid "Support for the updated Accelerate BLAS/LAPACK library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:27
msgid "The Python versions supported in this release are 3.9-3.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:31
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:34
msgid "Array API v2022.12 support in ``numpy.array_api``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:36
msgid ""
"``numpy.array_api`` now full supports the `v2022.12 version <https://data-"
"apis.org/array-api/2022.12>`__ of the array API standard. Note that this "
"does not yet include the optional ``fft`` extension in the standard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:41
msgid "(`gh-23789 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/23789>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:45
msgid ""
"Support for the updated Accelerate BLAS/LAPACK library, including ILP64 (64-"
"bit integer) support, in macOS 13.3 has been added. This brings arm64 "
"support, and significant performance improvements of up to 10x for commonly "
"used linear algebra operations. When Accelerate is selected at build time, "
"the 13.3+ version will automatically be used if available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:51
msgid "(`gh-24053 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/24053>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:54
msgid "``meson`` backend for ``f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:55
msgid ""
"``f2py`` in compile mode (i.e. ``f2py -c``) now accepts the ``--backend "
"meson`` option. This is the default option for Python ``3.12`` on-wards. "
"Older versions will still default to ``--backend distutils``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:59
msgid ""
"To support this in realistic use-cases, in compile mode ``f2py`` takes a ``--"
"dep`` flag one or many times which maps to ``dependency()`` calls in the "
"``meson`` backend, and does nothing in the ``distutils`` backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:63
msgid ""
"There are no changes for users of ``f2py`` only as a code generator, i.e. "
"without ``-c``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:66
msgid "(`gh-24532 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/24532>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:69
msgid "``bind(c)`` support for ``f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:70
msgid ""
"Both functions and subroutines can be annotated with ``bind(c)``. ``f2py`` "
"will handle both the correct type mapping, and preserve the unique label for "
"other ``C`` interfaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:74
msgid ""
"**Note:** ``bind(c, name = 'routine_name_other_than_fortran_routine')`` is "
"not honored by the ``f2py`` bindings by design, since ``bind(c)`` with the "
"``name`` is meant to guarantee only the same name in ``C`` and ``Fortran``, "
"not in ``Python`` and ``Fortran``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:79 ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:91
msgid "(`gh-24555 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/24555>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:83
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:86
msgid "``iso_c_binding`` support for ``f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:87
msgid ""
"Previously, users would have to define their own custom ``f2cmap`` file to "
"use type mappings defined by the Fortran2003 ``iso_c_binding`` intrinsic "
"module. These type maps are now natively supported by ``f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:95
msgid "Build system changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:97
msgid ""
"In this release, NumPy has switched to Meson as the build system and meson-"
"python as the build backend. Installing NumPy or building a wheel can be "
"done with standard tools like ``pip`` and ``pypa/build``. The following are "
"supported:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:102
msgid ""
"Regular installs: ``pip install numpy`` or (in a cloned repo) ``pip install ."
"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:104
msgid "Building a wheel: ``python -m build`` (preferred), or ``pip wheel .``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:105
msgid "Editable installs: ``pip install -e . --no-build-isolation``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:106
msgid ""
"Development builds through the custom CLI implemented with `spin <https://"
"github.com/scientific-python/spin>`__: ``spin build``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:109
msgid ""
"All the regular ``pip`` and ``pypa/build`` flags (e.g., ``--no-build-"
"isolation``) should work as expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:113
msgid "NumPy-specific build customization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:115
msgid ""
"Many of the NumPy-specific ways of customizing builds have changed. The "
"``NPY_*`` environment variables which control BLAS/LAPACK, SIMD, threading, "
"and other such options are no longer supported, nor is a ``site.cfg`` file "
"to select BLAS and LAPACK. Instead, there are command-line flags that can be "
"passed to the build via ``pip``/``build``'s config-settings interface. These "
"flags are all listed in the ``meson_options.txt`` file in the root of the "
"repo. Detailed documented will be available before the final 1.26.0 release; "
"for now please see `the SciPy \"building from source\" docs <http://scipy."
"github.io/devdocs/building/index.html>`__ since most build customization "
"works in an almost identical way in SciPy as it does in NumPy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:127
msgid "Build dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:129
msgid ""
"While the runtime dependencies of NumPy have not changed, the build "
"dependencies have. Because we temporarily vendor Meson and meson-python, "
"there are several new dependencies - please see the ``[build-system]`` "
"section of ``pyproject.toml`` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:135
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.0-notes.rst:137
msgid ""
"This build system change is quite large. In case of unexpected issues, it is "
"still possible to use a ``setup.py``-based build as a temporary workaround "
"(on Python 3.9-3.11, not 3.12), by copying ``pyproject.toml.setuppy`` to "
"``pyproject.toml``. However, please open an issue with details on the NumPy "
"issue tracker. We aim to phase out ``setup.py`` builds as soon as possible, "
"and therefore would like to see all potential blockers surfaced early on in "
"the 1.26.0 release cycle."
msgstr ""

